                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="major" script="thuluth naskh">
                        <desc><label>Script: </label>Apart from fol. 1b and fol. 25b, there are
                           three lines of fine calligraphic thuluth script interspersed with two
                           groups of two lines of calligraphic naskh script.</desc>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>Fol. 1b contains a title heading panel in blue and gold. Sentences
                        throughout are punctuated with small gold, red, and blue
                        florettes. Text box in red, blue and gold lines.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <p>Eastern binding with envelope flap severely damaged with only portions of
                        the original leather remaining and the boards crumbling. Rear board has a
                        stamped medallion.</p>
                  </bindingDesc>
